created_at: the trader at the brokerage has to work the order during the day or in the case of ZIM over several days. They come in at 9:30 buying 10
column5: 000 shares in a print while trying not to alert momentum traders because they don't want to run the stock up...yet. The trading dept in ZIM's case always steps away at about 11am and lets retail do what they do the rest of the day. Their tracks are on the tape if you look at the 1 minute chart over the past few days you'll see them. Same pattern. At the end of the day or first ting next morning you'll see a huge volume spike but that's not a trade
column6: it's a Cross trade when the brokerage house transfers the shares to his buyer at the average accumulation price. That's another sign of what is going on.
